articles.description: Clemson junior guard Shelton Mitchell is out of the hospital but remains in the concussion protocol following an injury suffered during Wednesday's loss to Florida State.
articles.headline: Clemson's Shelton Mitchell exits hospital after hit to head

articles.description: Mark Schlabach joins OTL to discuss the news that a U.S. District Court denied a motion to dismiss federal criminal charges against three of the 10 men arrested for their alleged roles in the FBI's two-year investigation into college basketball corruption
articles.headline: Court denies dismissal off CBB probe

articles.description: Reggie Lynch maintains his innocence against sexual misconduct allegations but has dropped appeals of his Minnesota expulsion because he does not feel he could receive a fair hearing.
articles.headline: Reggie Lynch drops appeals of sexual misconduct rulings, accepts expulsion

articles.description: A U.S. District Court judge denied a motion Thursday to dismiss federal criminal charges against former Adidas executives James Gatto and Merl Code and former sports agent Christian Dawkins in the FBI's investigation into college basketball corruption.
articles.headline: Judge denies motion to drop charges in corruption case against ex-Adidas execs, agent

articles.description: With Kentucky missing an edge, along with a couple of pieces, could the reeling Wildcats miss the NCAA tourney for the second time under John Calipari?
articles.headline: Is this John Calipari's most disappointing Kentucky team ever?

articles.description: Have Oklahoma's recent troubles made Trae Young not a sure thing for the Wooden Award? Arizona's Deandre Ayton is among the players who might get another look.
articles.headline: Wooden Watch: Can someone catch Trae Young?

images.name: Greenberg would take Sexton over Young for NBA

videos.description: Trevon Bluiett gets the rebound and finds Kaiser Gates down court who makes the bucket for Xavier.
videos.headline: Bluiett connects with Gates for fast-break layup

videos.description: Justin Roberts gets past J.P. Macura and makes the jumper to tie the game against Xavier.
videos.headline: DePaul's Roberts beats Macura with quick jumper

videos.description: DePaul gets a turnover and Max Strus drains a 3-pointer on the other end to extend DePaul's early lead over Xavier.
videos.headline: DePaul stays hot with Strus 3-pointer

videos.description: Quentin Goodin drives in for the layup and draws contact as Xavier tries to come back against DePaul.
videos.headline: Goodin answers with and-1 bucket

videos.description: Kerem Kanter rebounds and finds Trevon Bluiett down court who finishes with the layup for Xavier.
videos.headline: Bluiett energizes crowd with fast layup

videos.description: Quentin Goodin intercepts a pass and throws it down on the other end for Xavier.
videos.headline: Goodin gets big steal and slam vs. DePaul

videos.description: Jordan Roberts blocks a shot and finds a way to gain control of the ball to give DePaul possession.
videos.headline: Roberts shuts down Xavier with big block

videos.description: J.P. Macura intercepts a pass and gets it to Quentin Goodin who elevates for the slam to extend Xavier's lead in the final seconds.
videos.headline: Xavier seals win with steal-and-slam
